# Mockup UI — use established patterns

**Default to the design system.** Only deviate when the user explicitly asks for a variant.

## Source of truth (check in this order)

1. **`css/components.css`** — cards, filters, tables, buttons, `.card-header`, `.card-title`, `.filter-panel`
2. **`css/layout.css`** — `.panels-container`, `.table-wrapper`, page layout
3. **Sibling screen in the same product area** — e.g. CI Portfolio for CI grids; Trades for title date filter
4. **Product CSS** — `css/fund-allocations.css` (FA shell), `css/trades.css`, `css/certificate-inventory.css`

If something looks wrong, **compare a reference screen first** — do not invent local fixes.

## Do not go rogue

- **No one-off font sizes, padding, or spacing** when a shared class or sibling screen already defines the pattern
- **No duplicated CSS blocks** — extend existing selectors (`body.ci-portfolio-page …, body.ci-registry-page …`) or link the stylesheet that already owns the pattern
- **No renames of shared patterns** — e.g. use `trade-date-filter` + `trades.css`, not a copy like `ci-title-date-filter`
- **Override only what the layout requires** — e.g. filter panel inside a card may need transparent bg / no side borders; still use standard bottom spacing

## Common patterns (not optional one-offs)

| Element | Standard |
|--------|----------|
| **Card title** | `.card-title` — 16px, 600 (`components.css`). Not filters-card 13px. |
| **Card header height** | `.fa-main-shell .card-header`: `min-height: 40px`, `padding: 0 1em`. Use when the header has no ~29px action buttons (summary-only headers collapse without this). |
| **Filter panel spacing** | Global `.filter-panel` padding + page rule **`padding-bottom: var(--spacing-lg)`** only (Portfolio, Invoicing). Do not zero bottom padding. |
| **Title date filter** | Trades `trade-date-filter` classes + `css/trades.css` (Registry Activity included there). |
| **Page header** | `.page-header` > `.page-header__title-row` (or product alias with same class, e.g. `.fa-alloc-title-line.page-header__title-row`, `.act-title-line.page-header__title-row`). Fixed **32px** min row height + **12px** bottom margin via `components.css` — required on **every** screen, with or without as-of picker / date strip / title filter. |
| **As-of picker** | Shared `as-of-picker` in page header title row (`css/as-of-picker.css`, `js/as-of-picker.js`). Use `initAsOfPicker()`; FA may pass custom `renderCalendar` for allocation-status cells. Not a filter-card date input. |
| **CI grids** | Share Portfolio grid / status / row-menu rules in `certificate-inventory.css`; row menu opens to the right (Trades/Invoicing pattern). |
| **Table inset** | `panels-container` uses `padding: 1em`. If nested in a card without panels-container, use `1em` — not ad hoc `--spacing-lg` unless matching an existing screen. |

## Copy — Title Case for labels, card titles, and table headers

Use **Title Case** for user-visible label text in mockups (not sentence case).

**Applies to:**
- `.form-label` (modals, forms, detail panels)
- `.filter-label` (filter rows)
- `.card-title` and `.fa-card-title-text` (card headers, collapsible filter cards, pane titles)
- Card titles rendered in JS (`card-title` HTML strings)
- **Table column headers** — `<th>` in HTML and grid head strings in JS (`ciRegistryHeadHtml`, `renderHead`, etc.)

**Title Case means:** capitalize each principal word. Match sibling screens (Portfolio, Trades, FA).

| ✅ | ❌ |
|----|-----|
| Activity Log | Activity log |
| Serial Numbers | Serial numbers |
| Serial Range | Serial range |
| Counterparty / Beneficiary | Counterparty / beneficiary |
| Fuel Type | Fuel type |
| As Of | As of |
| Find Trade | Find trade |
| Submitted | submitted |

**Exceptions (keep as-is):**
- **Page titles** (`.page-title`, `h1`) — often ALL CAPS per Mirage chrome; follow the reference screen
- **Proper nouns, acronyms, units** — e.g. `MWh`, `Registry`, `PJM-GATS`
- **Phrases with slashes or parentheses** — e.g. `Linked / Unlinked`, `Volume (MWh)`, `Cost Basis ($/MWh)`
- **Empty or icon-only `<th>`** — e.g. kabob menu column with `aria-label` only

When adding or editing HTML/JS strings, scan labels, card titles, and **table headers** before finishing.

## Typography — no monospace unless requested

**Default: sans-serif** (Figtree via page `<link>`, `font-family: inherit` in components). Grids, forms, filters, and card copy use the standard UI font.

**Do not use monospace** unless the user explicitly asks for it or you are matching an existing screen that already uses mono for that element.

Avoid:
- `font-family: monospace` / `ui-monospace` / Menlo / Consolas on tables, cells, labels, or headers
- Inline `style="font-family: monospace"` on mockup HTML
- Adding `.mono` or `--font-mono` outside FA areas that already define them

FA-only: `.mono` and `var(--font-mono)` exist in `fund-allocations.css` for specific allocation/true-up cases — do not spread that pattern to Certificate Inventory, Trades chrome, Invoicing, etc. without instruction.

## When a layout differs from the reference

Document **why** in a short CSS comment and keep the diff minimal (e.g. “filter inside card — transparent panel only”). Prefer markup that matches the reference (filter-panel + panels-container) unless the user chose a different structure.
